<mxfile host="drawio_tools.py">
  <diagram id="page_kanban_board" name="Kanban Board">
    <mxGraphModel dx="1200" dy="800" grid="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="3000" pageHeight="2000" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="0" />
        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />
        <mxCell id="2" value="&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-top:4px;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;kanban board&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ records a timestamp each time it is saved&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ defines an ordered set of stages, each with a scope level and an ordered list of skills : stages, scope level, skills&lt;br/&gt;+ is the single source of truth for which skills each stage requires — skill progress entries on a ticket are populated from it when work starts, never duplicated : skills, stage, skill progress, ticket&lt;br/&gt;+ tickets flow through its stages; skills act on each ticket at its current stage : tickets, stages, skills, ticket, stage&lt;br/&gt;+ is acted upon by a team — the number of executor/reviewer pairs per agent role : team, agent role&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:9px;color:#666;&quot;&gt;&lt;i&gt;every ticket occupies exactly one stage at any given time&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="verticalAlign=top;align=left;overflow=fill;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="459" y="744" width="260" height="150" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="3" value="&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-top:4px;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;ticket&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ carries a unique identifier and a lineage tracing its ancestry from project through finer scope levels : lineage, scope levels&lt;br/&gt;+ has a board position — either backlog, the stage it currently occupies, or complete : board position, stage&lt;br/&gt;+ holds a scope level matching its current stage&amp;#x27;s scope in the kanban board : scope level, stage&amp;#x27;s, kanban board&lt;br/&gt;+ maintains a priority determining its ordering within the backlog, derived from the story map and thin-slicing : priority&lt;br/&gt;+ tracks skill progress for each skill an agent starts work on — entries are created when work starts : skill progress, skill, agent&lt;br/&gt;+ waits in stage done after all skills complete — does not advance automatically; a team member with the first skill of the next stage picks it up : stage done,  after all ,  complete — does not advance automatically; a ,  member with the first ,  of the next &lt;br/&gt;+ when picked up from stage done, either advances to the next same-scope stage or scatters — archives itself and creates child tickets at the finer scope level, each entering backlog : stage, stage, scatters,  — archives itself and creates child ,  at the finer &lt;br/&gt;+ scattered child tickets carry a reference to their parent ticket and a priority from the story map : tickets, ticket&lt;br/&gt;+ records timestamps for when it entered and completed each stage : stage&lt;br/&gt;+ carries free-text notes that may signal blocked status : notes&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:9px;color:#666;&quot;&gt;&lt;i&gt;the kanban board is the single source of truth for which skills a stage requires...&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;i&gt;a ticket&amp;#x27;s scope level must match the scope declared by its current stage in the...&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;i&gt;scatter only occurs when the next stage&amp;#x27;s scope level is finer than the current&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="verticalAlign=top;align=left;overflow=fill;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="299" y="1396" width="260" height="262" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="4" value="&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-top:4px;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;board position&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ is the stage a ticket currently occupies on the kanban board : stage, ticket, kanban board&lt;br/&gt;+ a ticket with no stage yet is in backlog; a ticket that has passed all stages is complete : ticket, stage, ticket, stages&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:9px;color:#666;&quot;&gt;&lt;i&gt;a ticket never advances to the next stage automatically — a team member must pic...&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="verticalAlign=top;align=left;overflow=fill;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="168" y="1818" width="260" height="102" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="5" value="&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-top:4px;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;skill progress&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ is created by the stage on the ticket when an agent starts work on a skill — not before : stage, ticket, agent, skill&lt;br/&gt;+ tracks execution status through not started ? in progress ? done : execution status&lt;br/&gt;+ tracks review status through not started ? in progress ? done (or failed, triggering rework) : review status&lt;br/&gt;+ records the agent role performing execution and the agent role performing review, plus start and end timestamps for both : agent role, agent role&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:9px;color:#666;&quot;&gt;&lt;i&gt;execution status must reach done before review status can transition from not st...&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;i&gt;a stage is complete only when every skill defined in the kanban board for that s...&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="verticalAlign=top;align=left;overflow=fill;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="528" y="1818" width="260" height="150" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="6" value="&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-top:4px;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;focus skill&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ drives the bot or magnifying-glass icon on the ticket card face and the active row in the expanded skill list&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ is the skill the board highlights on a ticket card and expanded skill list : skill, ticket&lt;br/&gt;+ when a skill is under review, the focus skill is that reviewing skill : skill, focus skill, skill&lt;br/&gt;+ when a skill is executing, the focus skill is that executing skill : skill, focus skill, skill&lt;br/&gt;+ when an active ticket sits in in progress at a stage with no skill currently executing or under review, the focus skill is the first incomplete skill in stage work required order : ticket, in progress,  at a ,  with no skill currently executing or under review, the ,  is the first incomplete ,  in &lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="verticalAlign=top;align=left;overflow=fill;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="819" y="744" width="260" height="126" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7" value="&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-top:4px;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;display focus&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ is the focus skill shown on a ticket after per-role WIP from team capacity is applied : focus skill, ticket, team&lt;br/&gt;+ when multiple active tickets at the same stage compete for the same agent role, only the highest-priority tickets up to the role&amp;#x27;s executor count receive display focus for idle next-skill highlighting : tickets, stage, agent role, tickets, display focus, skill&lt;br/&gt;+ live execution or review always receives display focus regardless of WIP rank : display focus&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="verticalAlign=top;align=left;overflow=fill;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="569" y="370" width="260" height="94" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="8" value="&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-top:4px;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;role engagement&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ is the count of active tickets where an agent role is currently engaged : tickets, agent role&lt;br/&gt;+ a ticket engages a role when an agent of that role is executing or reviewing a skill, or when the ticket holds display focus on a skill that requires that role : ticket, agent, skill, ticket, display focus, skill&lt;br/&gt;+ drives how many agent-pool avatar slots display as &amp;quot;working&amp;quot; for each agent role : agent role&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="verticalAlign=top;align=left;overflow=fill;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="432" y="60" width="260" height="94" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="9" value="&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-top:4px;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;pool avatar state&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ is the visual liveness of an avatar in the agent pool: working, idle, or inactive : working, , , idle, , or , inactive&lt;br/&gt;+ working — role is engaged on the board (lit with role-color ring) : working&lt;br/&gt;+ idle — role is available (lit, no ring) : idle&lt;br/&gt;+ inactive — role is stale: heartbeat age exceeds the threshold and the role has zero board engagement (dim) : inactive,  — role is stale: &lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="verticalAlign=top;align=left;overflow=fill;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="792" y="60" width="260" height="110" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="10" value="&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-top:4px;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;stage&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ is a named phase of delivery work: context, shaping, discovery, exploration, specification, or engineering — always in that order&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ is a column on the kanban board; each ticket occupies exactly one stage : kanban board, ticket, stage&lt;br/&gt;+ carries a scope level defined by the kanban board : scope level, kanban board&lt;br/&gt;+ has a queue — tickets from the previous stage&amp;#x27;s done waiting to be picked up; a team member with the first required skill can take a ticket from the queue : queue,  — ,  from the previous , &amp;#x27;s done waiting to be picked up; a ,  member with the first required ,  can take a &lt;br/&gt;+ has in progress — tickets at this stage where skill work is underway : in progress,  — ,  at this ,  where &lt;br/&gt;+ has done — tickets at this stage where all skills are complete, waiting for pickup to the next stage : done,  — ,  at this ,  where all ,  are complete, waiting for pickup to the next &lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:9px;color:#666;&quot;&gt;&lt;i&gt;a ticket cannot skip a stage or move backward&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;i&gt;a ticket in the queue of stage N was in the done state of stage N-1&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="verticalAlign=top;align=left;overflow=fill;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="258" y="1054" width="260" height="182" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="11" value="&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-top:4px;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;stage work required&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ is the ordered list of skills required by a stage : skills, stage&lt;br/&gt;+ each skill is performed by an agent role : skill, agent role&lt;br/&gt;+ describes what work a ticket at each stage requires : ticket, stage&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="verticalAlign=top;align=left;overflow=fill;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="99" y="744" width="260" height="94" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="12" value="&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-top:4px;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;team&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ is the executor/reviewer pair counts per agent role configured on the board : agent role&lt;br/&gt;+ holds a count per agent role that can be incremented or decremented : agent role&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:9px;color:#666;&quot;&gt;&lt;i&gt;pair counts must be non-negative integers&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;i&gt;defaults to one executor and one reviewer per agent role when not explicitly con...&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="verticalAlign=top;align=left;overflow=fill;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="618" y="1054" width="260" height="118" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="13" value="&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-top:4px;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;board mode&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ is a setting on the kanban board that determines whether the kanban lead acts automatically or waits for user-directed action intents : kanban board, kanban lead, action intents&lt;br/&gt;+ defaults to automatic — the kanban lead pulls, scatters, and advances tickets without intervention : kanban lead, tickets&lt;br/&gt;+ when set to manual, suppresses all automatic kanban lead actions — pull, scatter, and advance wait for explicit action intents : kanban lead, action intents&lt;br/&gt;+ persists as part of the kanban board configuration alongside stages and team : kanban board, stages, team&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:9px;color:#666;&quot;&gt;&lt;i&gt;the kanban board is always in exactly one board mode — automatic or manual — nev...&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="verticalAlign=top;align=left;overflow=fill;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="1152" y="60" width="260" height="134" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="14" value="&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-top:4px;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;action intent&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ is a record written to the action state file by the app when the Delivery Lead assigns a team member agent to a ticket in manual mode : action state file, app, team member agent, ticket, manual mode&lt;br/&gt;+ specifies which skill to execute on which ticket and which team member agent should perform the work : skill, ticket, team member agent&lt;br/&gt;+ is consumed by the kanban lead when it detects a change in the action state file : kanban lead, action state file&lt;br/&gt;+ triggers the kanban lead to delegate skill execution to the named team member agent : kanban lead, skill, team member agent&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:9px;color:#666;&quot;&gt;&lt;i&gt;an action intent is only written when the kanban board is in manual mode&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;i&gt;the specified skill must be one required by the ticket&amp;#x27;s current stage&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="verticalAlign=top;align=left;overflow=fill;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="72" y="60" width="260" height="150" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="15" value="&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-top:4px;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;action state file&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ lives alongside board.json in the kanban directory&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ is the file the app writes action intents to and the kanban lead watches for changes : app, action intents, kanban lead&lt;br/&gt;+ is the communication channel between the app (writing) and the kanban lead (reading) : app, kanban lead&lt;br/&gt;+ is watched by the kanban lead for changes that signal new action intents to process : kanban lead, action intents&lt;br/&gt;+ Stage, ticket, board position, skill progress, stage work required, and team all belong here — none has meaning outside the kanban board (independence test). : Stage, ticket, board position, skill progress, stage work required, team, kanban board&lt;br/&gt;+ Scatter is an operation on ticket, not a standalone concept — its mechanics and invariant live on the ticket block (typing call). : Scatter, ticket, ticket&lt;br/&gt;+ Individual stage names are instances of stage, not subtypes (typing call). : stage&lt;br/&gt;+ Board mode, action intent, and action state file belong here — they govern how the kanban board operates and have no meaning outside it (independence test). : Board mode, action intent, action state file, kanban board&lt;br/&gt;+ Board mode is a setting on the kanban board, not a separate concept or subtype — automatic and manual are values, not types (typing call). : Board mode, kanban board&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:9px;color:#666;&quot;&gt;&lt;i&gt;only the app writes to the action state file; only the kanban lead reads from it&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="verticalAlign=top;align=left;overflow=fill;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="209" y="370" width="260" height="214" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="16" value="" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=1;endArrow=open;endSize=12;html=1;exitX=0.15;exitY=1;entryX=0.15;entryY=0;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" edge="1" parent="1" source="2" target="10">
