  <diagram id="page_agent_and_skills" name="Agent and Skills">
    <mxGraphModel dx="1200" dy="800" grid="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="3000" pageHeight="2000" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="0" />
        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />
        <mxCell id="2" value="&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-top:4px;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;skill&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ is a named practice method an agent executes on a ticket — e.g. `abd-domain-language`, `abd-story-acceptance-criteria`, `abd-clean-code` : agent, ticket&lt;br/&gt;+ is required by a stage through stage work required : stage, stage work required&lt;br/&gt;+ is performed by an agent role : agent role&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="verticalAlign=top;align=left;overflow=fill;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="60" y="60" width="260" height="94" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="3" value="&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-top:4px;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;agent&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ is an autonomous worker that starts work on skills for active tickets and drives them to done : skills, tickets&lt;br/&gt;+ has a work role — either executor or reviewer : work role&lt;br/&gt;+ as executor: does the skill work on the ticket : skill, ticket&lt;br/&gt;+ as reviewer: checks the skill work on the ticket : skill, ticket&lt;br/&gt;+ operates under one of four named delivery roles — product-owner, business-expert, ux-designer, or engineer — which determines which skills it can start work on : skills&lt;br/&gt;+ is constrained by its role&amp;#x27;s team count — the number of executors and reviewers that may work concurrently : team&lt;br/&gt;+ reports liveness by writing a heartbeat : heartbeat&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:9px;color:#666;&quot;&gt;&lt;i&gt;an agent may only start work on skills that require its role&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;i&gt;the kanban lead is a separate orchestrating role, not an agent&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="verticalAlign=top;align=left;overflow=fill;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="60" y="314" width="260" height="198" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="4" value="&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-top:4px;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;heartbeat&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ age is the elapsed seconds since it was last written&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ is a timestamp written by each agent and the kanban lead recording last activity : agent, kanban lead&lt;br/&gt;+ determines agent liveness together with board engagement: stale heartbeat dims avatars only when the role has zero board engagement : agent, heartbeat&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:9px;color:#666;&quot;&gt;&lt;i&gt;an agent pool avatar is *inactive only when heartbeat age exceeds the staleness ...&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="verticalAlign=top;align=left;overflow=fill;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="60" y="672" width="260" height="118" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="5" value="&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-top:4px;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;kanban lead&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ manages the kanban board — the single orchestrating role above the four delivery roles : kanban board&lt;br/&gt;+ detects when a stage is complete and triggers scatter when needed : stage, scatter&lt;br/&gt;+ monitors heartbeats to determine which agents are alive : heartbeats, agents&lt;br/&gt;+ pulls tickets from the backlog into the first stage : tickets, stage&lt;br/&gt;+ reads board mode setting before acting — in manual mode, suppresses automatic pull, scatter, and advance actions : board mode, manual mode&lt;br/&gt;+ watches the action state file for changes written by the app : action state file, app&lt;br/&gt;+ delegates skill execution to the appropriate team member agent based on action intents : skill, team member agent, action intents&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="verticalAlign=top;align=left;overflow=fill;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="60" y="950" width="260" height="158" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="6" value="&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-top:4px;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;team member agent&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;+ is an agent operating in one of the four delivery roles (product-owner, business-expert, ux-designer, engineer) that the kanban lead delegates skill execution to : agent, kanban lead, skill&lt;br/&gt;+ executes a single assigned skill on a ticket when directed by the kanban lead via an action intent : skill, ticket, kanban lead, action intent&lt;br/&gt;+ advances the ticket to in progress when it starts executing its first skill : ticket, skill&lt;br/&gt;+ persists skill completion to the board state upon finishing execution : skill&lt;br/&gt;+ completes the ticket when all skills at its current stage are finished : ticket, skills, stage&lt;br/&gt;+ is distinguished from the kanban lead which orchestrates but does not execute skills : kanban lead, skills&lt;br/&gt;+ Skill and agent are the core concepts — role, executor/reviewer variant, and team constraint are properties of the agent, not separate concepts (independence test). : Skill, agent, team, agent&lt;br/&gt;+ Heartbeat belongs here — it exists to report agent liveness and has no meaning outside agent monitoring (independence test). Age and liveness determination are properties of the heartbeat, not a separate concept. : Heartbeat, agent, agent, heartbeat&lt;br/&gt;+ Individual role names are instances of the role property on agent, not subtypes (typing call). : agent&lt;br/&gt;+ Kanban lead orchestrates the board but its full behavior belongs to the Kanban Lead module (scope-fit test). : Kanban lead&lt;br/&gt;+ Team member agent belongs here — it is an agent distinguished by its relationship to the kanban lead and action intents, not a separate type; the four delivery roles remain instances of the role property (typing call). : Team member agent, agent, kanban lead, action intents&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;/&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin:0px;margin-left:4px;font-size:9px;color:#666;&quot;&gt;&lt;i&gt;a team member agent only executes skills that match its delivery role&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="verticalAlign=top;align=left;overflow=fill;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="60" y="1268" width="260" height="246" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7" value="" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=1;endArrow=open;endSize=12;html=1;exitX=0.5;exitY=1;entryX=0.5;entryY=0;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" edge="1" parent="1" source="2" target="3">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="8" value="" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=1;endArrow=open;endSize=12;html=1;exitX=0.5;exitY=1;entryX=0.5;entryY=0;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" edge="1" parent="1" source="3" target="4">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="9" value="" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=1;endArrow=open;endSize=12;html=1;exitX=0.5;exitY=1;entryX=0.5;entryY=0;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" edge="1" parent="1" source="4" target="5">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="10" value="" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=1;endArrow=open;endSize=12;html=1;exitX=0.5;exitY=1;entryX=0.5;entryY=0;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" edge="1" parent="1" source="5" target="6">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
</mxfile>